item.title: CVE-2013-2011|2024-08-06T15:20:37.426Z -- super%20cache%20plugin -- super%20cache%20plugin
item.description: WordPress W3 Super Cache Plugin before 1.3.2 contains a PHP code-execution vulnerability which could allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary code. This issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2013-2009.
